‐ Don't ever retire.

38:45.404 --> 38:48.323
And Mr. Shatner,
he's living proof that‐‐

38:48.323 --> 38:49.741
load the docks, baby.

38:49.741 --> 38:51.827
Load the wagons
and keep it going.

38:51.827 --> 38:54.705
Kinda came into this thing
mentally kicking and screaming.

38:54.705 --> 38:56.915
Oh!
I'm not eating that [bleep].

38:56.915 --> 38:59.918
‐ You're being a child.
‐ Yeah, baby!

38:59.918 --> 39:02.337
But this trip really
did change my life.

39:02.337 --> 39:04.172
Welcome to Kyoto, boys!

39:04.172 --> 39:06.842
And for all of you right now
that are sitting back

39:06.842 --> 39:08.510
and you're eating
potato chips‐‐

39:08.510 --> 39:12.681
Oh, God, would I have
loved potato chips on this trip!

39:12.681 --> 39:16.101
I encourage you,
get up and explore the world.

39:16.101 --> 39:17.936
Hello, everyone.

39:17.936 --> 39:20.439
Ahh!
It will change you.

39:20.439 --> 39:24.359
And Shatner's right,
change is good.

39:24.359 --> 39:26.111
But don't tell him that.

39:26.111 --> 39:27.529
‐ I'll say one thing.

39:27.529 --> 39:30.032
I wanna know more about
what Bill feels

39:30.032 --> 39:32.284
instead of about
what Bill knows.

39:32.284 --> 39:34.745
‐ Nobody asked me.
‐ How do you feel?

39:34.745 --> 39:38.373
‐ [clears throat]
‐ [laughing]

39:38.373 --> 39:42.210
‐ In my somewhat longer life
than yours,

39:42.210 --> 39:44.212
I have never
and would never

39:44.212 --> 39:47.549
have experienced
what we have done together.

39:47.549 --> 39:49.301
Hah!
‐ Oh!

39:49.301 --> 39:53.055
‐ Five weeks, living
with somebody 24 hours a day‐‐

39:53.055 --> 39:55.474
Why do I think of peaches?
‐ [laughs]

39:55.474 --> 39:57.559
‐ Will either make you
or break you.

39:57.559 --> 40:00.562
This made it for me,
in terms of friends.

40:00.562 --> 40:02.397
[all laughing]

40:02.397 --> 40:06.234
‐ I look forward to sitting
at another table,

40:06.234 --> 40:09.738
wherever it may be,
with the four of you.

40:09.738 --> 40:12.074
‐ Hear, hear!
‐ Good toast.

40:12.074 --> 40:13.033
‐ ♪ Surrender ♪

40:13.033 --> 40:14.910
‐ Cheers.

40:14.910 --> 40:16.286
‐ Here's to the big time.

40:16.286 --> 40:17.788
♪ ♪

40:17.788 --> 40:19.122
["Cecilia and the Satellite"
playing]

40:19.122 --> 40:20.540
‐ All right,
I'm lighting mine.

40:20.540 --> 40:22.334
One of things they do
in Thailand,

40:22.334 --> 40:23.877
when you're at the end
of your journey,

40:23.877 --> 40:25.587
you make a wish,
you write it down,

40:25.587 --> 40:27.005
you put it in the lantern

40:27.005 --> 40:29.174
and the lantern
takes it into the heavens.

40:29.174 --> 40:31.093
Hey, guys, we got ours lit.
How you doing?

40:31.093 --> 40:33.095
‐ The paper is too close
to the flame.

40:33.095 --> 40:34.513
‐ How's that?

40:34.513 --> 40:36.431
We also sent one
floating down a river.

40:36.431 --> 40:37.849
Remember that?

40:37.849 --> 40:40.268
What happens
when it catches on fire?

40:40.268 --> 40:41.436
Oh, my God!

40:41.436 --> 40:43.105
‐ Whose is that?
‐ That's yours.

40:43.105 --> 40:44.439
Look at it burning up.

40:44.439 --> 40:47.442
[laughing]
Poor Bill.

40:47.442 --> 40:49.778
‐ Okay, let it go.
See what happens.

40:49.778 --> 40:51.113
♪ ♪

40:51.113 --> 40:53.532
‐ Best wishes.

40:53.532 --> 40:54.783
Oh, they're all around us.

40:54.783 --> 40:56.118
‐ Look at this.
‐ Magic.

40:56.118 --> 40:58.829
‐ How wonderful
is this night.

40:58.829 --> 41:00.580
♪ ♪

41:00.580 --> 41:02.624
Well, we did it.

41:02.624 --> 41:04.292
‐ ♪ Oh oh‐oh oh oh‐oh ♪

41:04.292 --> 41:05.710
[thudding]
‐ Oh!

41:05.710 --> 41:07.629
‐ [bleep]

41:07.629 --> 41:09.381
‐ The five of us came
on this journey

41:09.381 --> 41:13.718
to learn about a culture
we didn't understand.

41:13.718 --> 41:15.637
‐ Oh, my God!

41:15.637 --> 41:17.806
‐ Oh! Oh!
‐ [yells]

41:17.806 --> 41:18.890
♪ ♪

41:18.890 --> 41:20.475
What we didn't expect was

41:20.475 --> 41:23.645
that we would learn
about ourselves and each other.

41:23.645 --> 41:26.148
‐ ♪ If I could fly ♪
‐ Whoa!

41:26.148 --> 41:27.983
‐ ♪ Than I would know ♪
‐ This is style, man.

41:27.983 --> 41:29.651
[laughter]

41:29.651 --> 41:30.986
‐ ♪ What life looks like
from up above ♪

41:30.986 --> 41:32.571
♪ And down below ♪

41:32.571 --> 41:35.157
‐ We started off in Los Angeles
as friends,

41:35.157 --> 41:38.493
and we're going back
to our home as family.

41:38.493 --> 41:42.956
‐ ♪ I'm the satellite ♪
‐ ♪ Oh oh‐oh oh oh‐oh ♪

41:42.956 --> 41:44.499
♪ And you're the sky ♪

41:44.499 --> 41:46.334
‐ Look how beautiful this is.

41:46.334 --> 41:48.503
‐ What is the reason
we did this?

41:48.503 --> 41:50.630
‐ To make a wish.
‐ The wish is...

41:50.630 --> 41:52.340
for more
and greater adventures.

41:52.340 --> 41:53.508
‐ Put it right here.
‐ Right there.

41:53.508 --> 41:54.676
‐ Right there.
‐ Right there.

41:54.676 --> 41:56.595
‐ One, two, three!
[all yell]

41:56.595 --> 41:58.096
‐ ♪ Oh oh‐oh oh oh‐oh ♪

41:58.096 --> 41:59.347
‐ Well, a lot of wishes
out there.

41:59.347 --> 42:01.433
‐ Look!
It's catching on fire!

42:01.433 --> 42:03.018
Oh, my God!

42:03.018 --> 42:04.352
Kidding.
[laughing]

42:04.352 --> 42:06.771
‐ ♪ And you're the sky ♪

42:06.771 --> 42:08.857
♪ ♪
